    "Q6: Full scan lineitem with vectorized SIMD filtering (discount + quantity predicates). Single-pass sum aggregation. Use morsel-driven parallelism (64 cores).",
    "Q7: Nation subquery filter on 2 countries (high selectivity predicate). Hash join lineitem-orders-customer. Date extraction to year via O(1) epoch-day arithmetic.",
    "Q9: String pattern match (p_name LIKE '%green%') on 2M part table (~3% selectivity, ~60K rows). Hash join with partsupp, then orders. Partial aggregation by (nation, year).",
    "Q10: LEFT OUTER JOIN customer-orders. Filter on l_returnflag='R' (33% selectivity). Late materialization: filter + aggregate first, then fetch names/addresses. LIMIT 20 → early termination after sort.",
    "Q12: Join orders-lineitem, filter on l_shipmode IN (...) (40% selectivity) and temporal predicates. Zone-map pruning on l_receiptdate. Conditional aggregation (CASE) without materialization.",
    "Q13: LEFT OUTER JOIN with anti-pattern filter (comments). Two-pass aggregation: count per customer, then count distribution. Consider partial aggregation to reduce cardinality.",
    "Q16: Subquery IN (SELECT s_suppkey) requires semi-join. Build hash set from supplier subquery (filtered ~1% of 100K). Hash join with part, then COUNT(DISTINCT ps_suppkey) aggregation. Pre-compute supplier filter once.",
    "Q18: Subquery IN (SELECT l_orderkey) is correlated. Materialize inner result (expensive) OR execute subquery in first pass, then inner join. Use hash semi-join pattern. LIMIT 100 + sort.",
    "Q20: Nested subqueries with correlated joins. Decorrelate second subquery (0.5 * SUM per (partkey, suppkey)). Pre-compute lineitem aggregates by part/supplier. Semi-join on partsupp.",
    "Q21: Complex multi-existence-check (EXISTS l2, NOT EXISTS l3). Use semi-join for EXISTS, anti-join for NOT EXISTS. Materialize lineitem by orderkey to avoid repeated scans.",
    "Q22: Scalar subquery (AVG c_acctbal) executes once. Filter on country code substring (7 distinct values, ~14% total). Anti-join NOT EXISTS (orders). Partial aggregation by cntrycode."
