  "summary": "Workload dominated by lineitem (60M rows, 12 queries) and orders (15M rows, 10 queries) fact tables. Multi-way joins (3-6 tables) are critical path; filter selectivity varies 1%-96%. Aggregation cardinality ranges 1-1.5M groups (Q10, Q13 are memory-intensive). Subquery decorrelation (Q16, Q18, Q20, Q21) requires careful semi-join/anti-join optimization. Key levers: (1) early filtering on high-selectivity predicates (nation, region, date ranges), (2) hash join ordering to minimize intermediate cardinality, (3) partial aggregation + SIMD parallelism on fact scans, (4) semi-join reduction for EXISTS/IN subqueries."
